They do sit flush with the table, if, and only if, you screw around with them for 5 or 10 minutes to make them do so. To a first approximation, if you make the middle part parallel to the parts two spaces either side, and then make the end bit parallel to the one next to the middle piece on that side, it should lie flush.

However, easier said than done.
